graphs.text: # In this file, the alignment between the right and left halves of the
# second paragraph is based on line count, even though the lines on
# the right are shifted down by a varying amount (from 0.5 to 1.5
# baseline spacing). The misalignment is indicated by "{\} comments.
# The original C and F transcriptions used an alignment based on line
# position, where the right half of lines 4 through 9 were shifted
# down one line, with the spill over being transcribed as line 10.
# A case could be made for the two halves being independent paragraphs.
